The strongly elongated and filiform gonapophyses VIII, which considerably project over the apex of the anal segment (
Figs. 8–9
), and distinct praeopercular organ (
Fig. 8
) are shared with ♀♀ of Cranidiini . The developed gonoplacs and presence of a gula are in common with Cranidiini and Cladoxerini . A sister-group relationship with Cladoxerini (
Fig. 409
) is supported by the morphology of the profemora, fairly slender, stick-like body of ♀♀ and morphology of the eggs.
